<TITLE> 42 firms apply for international gateway licences </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 06 (bdnews24.com)  Forty-two companies have submitted bids to set up three international gateway exchanges in the private sector to route overseas calls in and out of Bangladesh. Thirty-nine firms have submitted bids for interconnection licences. Three companies will get licences for international gateways and two will get interconnection licences, Abbas Faruque, media consultant for Bangladesh Telecommunication Regulatory Commission, told bdnews24.com Thursday. The deadline for submission of international gateway bids was Dec 4, and the last date for interconnection licence bids ended on Dec 5. The new gateway exchanges are meant to break the monopoly of Bangladesh Telegraph and Telephone Board in the international call business. Applicants need to be resident in Bangladesh while existing telecom service providers have been banned from the bidding. bdn
